definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To remove unwanted vegetation from a cultivated area (especially grass).
( figurative , transitive ) To pilfer the best items from a collection.
( library science , transitive ) To systematically remove materials from a library collection based on a set of criteria.
examples: We usually weed romance novels that haven't circulated in over a year.
